REUTERS LIVE SERVICE PLUS ADVISORY FOR UNITED NATIONS GENERAL ASSEMBLY - TUESDAY TO MONDAY SEPTEMBER 19-25, 2017 
PLEASE NOTE THAT ALL PLANS ARE PROVISIONAL AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE
   From September 19-25, world leaders gather at the United Nations headquarters in New York for the annual General Assembly. Leaders' speeches will run live in full on the service.
    Please note attendees, speakers and schedule are subject to change. Please monitor for updates.
TUESDAY SEPTEMBER 19
TIME: 1300-1700GMT/ 1900-0100GMT
UN-ASSEMBLY/: 
UNITED NATIONS - World leaders gather as the United Nations General Debate opens with Brazil's President Michel Temer.  United States President Donald Trump, Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari, French President Emmanuel Macron, Colombia's President Juan Manuel Santos, Emir of Qatar Sheikh Tamim bin Hamad al-Thani, Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu are among those scheduled to speak in the first session.   In the afternoon session speakers include Polish President Andrzej Duda, Afghan President Ashraf Ghani and South Africa's President Jacob Zuma. (1300-1700GMT/1900-0100GMT) 
:: REUTERS/UNTV

UNITED NATIONS -  World leaders address the United Nations General Assembly. Egypt's President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and British Prime Minister Theresa May are among the expected speakers for the second day morning session.  Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, head of Libya's U.N. backed government Fayez al-Serraj will address the afternoon session. (1300-1700GMT/1900-0100GMT)
